12. THE MYTH OF LOWER--AND HIGHER--AIRFARES
    by Christopher Elliott

In the past several days, a number of would-be air travelers have
complained that airfares were on the upswing since terrorists felled
the World Trade Center towers and decimated the Pentagon. Truth is,
fares are likely to ease this month. But don't take my word for it.

For the full story, please visit
http://rd.SmarterLiving.com/da100401.12
<A HREF="rd.SmarterLiving.com/da100401.12">AOL</A>

~~~~~~~~~~~~

13. ASK ANITA: REDEEMING MILES ON AN AIRLINE THAT MAY GO BANKRUPT?
    by Anita Dunham-Potter, Contributing Travel Editor
   
Dear Anita,

I recently redeemed 70,000 frequent flier miles for two airline
tickets to Hawaii for next April. What happens if the airline I'm
supposed to fly on goes bankrupt? 

- Donna R., Columbia, SC

To read the answer, or to submit a question for Anita, visit
http://rd.SmarterLiving.com/da100401.13
<A HREF="rd.SmarterLiving.com/da100401.13">AOL</A>

