15. WHEN PICKING OUT SOUVENIRS, CONSIDER THE ORDINARY THINGS
    by Eoin O'Carroll

If the purpose of a souvenir is to serve as a token of remembrance of
a particular place, it's the ordinary things, not the touristy garbage,


that really count. By taking a few of these bits and pieces with you,
you might also take with you some happy memories. 

For the full story, please visit
http://rd.SmarterLiving.com/da100401.15
